BioSpecDescription: The portion of bone marrow concentrate of each patient not used for treatment will be sent to the biotechnology laboratory applied to the Orthopedics of the Institute Galeazzi and used for histological and molecular analysis. In particular, each sample will be characterized in terms of vitality, proliferation, cellular senescence, immunophenotype and differentiative capacity towards the osteogenic and chondrogenic lines. In addition, for each sample, the immunomodulatory activity exerted by the paracrine way in the presence of human chondrocytes stimulated by inflammatory conditions will be evaluated
